16.2.
Example:​ We manipulated the percentage of sugar by mass added to brownies. 
The four levels of this categorical variable are: 15%, 20%, 25%, or 40% cane 
sugar by mass.  
16.3.
More information​: For any experimental manipulation, you should give a precise 
definition of each manipulated variable. This must include a precise description of 
the levels at which each variable will be set, or a specific definition for each 
categorical treatment. For example, “loud or quiet,” should instead give either a 
precise decibel level or a means of recreating each level. 'Presence/absence' or 
'positive/negative' is an acceptable description if the variable is precisely 
