indices. Outliers will be included in the analysis.  
22.3.
More information​: Any rule for excluding a particular set of data is acceptable. 
One may describe rules for excluding a participant or for identifying outlier data. 
 
DATA EXCLUSIONS: 
 
Data from participants will be excluded if: 
1.
Both the PI and a research assistant will read each participant response on the self 
concept prompt and independently code their self concept response as either compliant 
or non compliant with their condition. These codes will be subjective and purely 

dichotomous. If both the PI and RA code a response as non-compliant, data for that 
participant will be excluded. If either party codes the response as compliant, the data will 
be included in all analyses. 
OR 
2.
The participant reports that they were unable to see the rating distribution image. 
OR 
3.
There is any missing data for the participant. 
